Minestrone

**adapted from Kenji's Minestrone recipe**

https://www.seriouseats.com/the-best-minestrone-soup-recipe

  - 2 qt chicken stock
  - 2 15 oz cans of white beans, drained & rinsed
  - 1 28 oz can of whole peeled tomatoes, smooshed up
  - 2-3 sprigs of thyme
  - 1-2 bay leaves
  - 4-5 cloves of garlic, finely minced
  - 1 large bunch kale (or other tough leafy green), destemmed & roughly chopped
  - 0.5 head cabbage
  - 2-3 carrots, chopped (or faux tourne)
  - 2-3 celery stalks, chopped
  - 1 onion, diced
  - 6 oz pancetta (or 4 oz bacon, cut into small lardons)
  - grated parmesan or pecorino cheese
  - olive oil, for drizzling
  - 1 parmesan rind
  - optional: all kinds of different veggies, to be added as appropriate in the cooking process
  - optional: 0.25 lbs ditalini or other small pasta

  (1) preheat oven to 300 degrees F
  (2) in dutch oven, gently crisp up pancetta, rendering fat
  (3) add onion, sweat until transparent
  (4) add garlic, cook until fragrant
  (5) add carrots, celery, and cabbage, cook until softened somewhat
  (6) add tomatoes, cook until simmering
  (7) add chicken stock, beans, thyme, bay leaves, and parmesan rind, bring back to simmer
  (8) cook in oven for ~45 minutes
  (9) remove from oven, add kale & pasta if using, cook for another 10 min
  (10) serve w sprinkled parmesan and olive oil lightly drizzled
